bug.short_desc: Some Legend Entries are not correct when the text is shortened by ellipsis

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 86284 report file
Build ID: I20071213-1700
Steps To Reproduce: 1.open the attached report 2.double click the chart to edit it 3.
More information: Some legend entries are overlapped.
Created attachment 86286 good screenshot without ellipsis

This happens only when the value text is visible, and is shortened with ellipsis. The overlapping is because the computation of the height is wrong in some case. Some legend text is also wrong, because the Label and ITextMetrics resource are shared between the legend text and value text, and the value is not set back in some case. I use separate resource for legend text and value text now. Anyway there are too many duplicated code in the function group computeHorizalByCategory ..., some computations are not consistent, for instance: In horizontal mode text ellipsis is not used, while in vertical mode is used. I have refactored the function group to reduce duplicated code and improve the clarity and consistency.
